Package com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse.discover

Discover data is described by the interfaces in this package.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AccessHistory
    Information about the access history for a content item.
    CMSDocument
    A document that is stored in a content management system (CMS) like SharePoint, Documentum, or LiveLink.
    ContentRoot
    A location in a content repository that serves as a starting point for a scan.
    DiscoverItem
    An item that was scanned by Network Discover.
    ExchangeItem
    An item that came from an Exchange server.
    FileServerItem
    Information about a file item that is stored on a file server.
    FileSystemItem
    A content item that comes from a file system.
    GenericContentItem
    The content item type for content that this crawled using the Web Services target.
    Locatable
    A content item or content container that can be located by a string identifier.
    LotusNotesItem
    A document from a LotusNotes repository.
    Permission
    An access permission on a content item.
    RemediatedItem
    An item implements this interface when remediation of the incident associated with it can include moving or copying the item to a new location.
    RemediationLocation
    The location to be used for remediating an item.
    ScanConfiguration
    The configuration of the scan associated with a given content item.
    SQLDatabaseRow
    A row in a SQL database.
    WebServerItem
    An item that was discovered on a web site.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Permission.Modifier
    Identifies whether a permission is being granted or revoked.
    Permission.Operation
    Identifies the type of permission.
    QuarantineType  
    TargetType
    This enumeration describes the different possible types of Discover targets.

Package com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse.discover Description

Discover data is described by the interfaces in this package. When handling an incident, you can use the Incident.getContentItem method to get access to these descriptors.
